        <obo:IAO_0000115>A tubular structure that transports secreted or excreted substances.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>A tube shaped portion of tissue lined with epithelial cells that collects secretions and routes them to their destination[ZFA:0005171].</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>Most ducts, but not all, are exocrine gland ducts. Some ontologies classify structures such as the oviduct here.</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
