            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A capillary tuft which forms a close network with the visceral epithelium (podocytes) and the mesangium to form the filtration barrier and is surrounded by Bowman&apos;s capsule in nephrons of the vertebrate kidney[GO].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>ZFA - The multi-tissue structure where the glomerular basement membrane supported by mesonephric podocytes filters blood from the glomerular capillaries. GUDMAP: &apos;Together, the Bowman&apos;s capsule and the glomerulus comprise the definitive renal corpuscle.&apos; - here the glomerulus is part of the capsule?</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <oboInOwl:created_by>Melissa Haendel</oboInOwl:created_by>
        <oboInOwl:creation_date>2009-06-18T09:26:37Z</oboInOwl:creation_date>
