            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Organism at the blastula stage - an early stage of embryonic development in animals. It is produced by cleavage of a fertilized ovum and consists of a spherical layer of around 128 cells surrounding a central fluid-filled cavity called the blastocoel. The blastula follows the morula and precedes the gastrula in the developmental sequence.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>TODO - check relationship with epiblast. Note in FMA this is not a subclass of embryo, but in uberon embryo is the whole organism from zygote onwards and thus includes the blastula</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>UBERON:0007011</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blastula"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>BILA:0000059</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>BTO:0000128</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>GAID:1294</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>MESH:A16.254.270.274</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>OGEM:000006</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>OpenCyc:Mx4rEetFnKP2EdqAAAACs4vPlg</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>blastula embryo</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>uberon</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>blastosphere</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>UBERON:0000307</oboInOwl:id>
