        <obo:IAO_0000115>The invaginated serous membrane that surrounds the lungs (the visceral portion) and lines the walls of the pleural cavity (parietal portion).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>The serous membrane that covers the lungs and lines the pleural cavity. [Kaufman_MH_and_Bard_JBL, The_anatomical_basis_of_mouse_development_(1999)_San_Diego:_Academic_Press, p.264][VHOG]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000007>pleural</obo:UBPROP_0000007>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>In MA, is_a cavity lining (which we equate to parietal). In FMA, is_a (viscous) serous membrane (which includes mesothelium plus connective tissue). Note the MA structure should probably be associated with the mesothelium of pleura in FMA. JB/EHDAA2 argues the term &apos;pleura&apos; is best used for the mesothelial lining (thus excluding connective tissue). See https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/86</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pleura"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://linkedlifedata.com/resource/umls/id/C0032225"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C12469"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://www.snomedbrowser.com/Codes/Details/181609007"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>BTO:0001791</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
