        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>consider splitting genitalia from reproductive system</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>Anatomical system which consists of organs and tissues associated with sexual reproduction of the organism.[AAO]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000003>Arguably, one of the most important aspects of urbilaterian organogenesis would have been gonadogenesis, since Urbilateria must have successfully generated gametes and developed a strategy for extrusion and fertilization, in order to be the ancestor of all living Bilateria.[well established][VHOG]</obo:UBPROP_0000003>
