        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>the tubules located between the bile canaliculi and interlobular bile ducts near the outer edge of a classic liver lobule</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>Note that this is part of the intrahepatic bile duct in MA, as this class is more alike the tree in FMA. Note also that SCT has canal of Hering and Entire IBduct as the only sibling terms under &apos;Structure of intralobular bile duct&apos; (i.e. the CoH is the only part of the entire IBduct)</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canals_of_Hering"/>
