        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#uberon_slim"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The nails of humans and the claws are moth are highly similar. Both species have a proximal nail fold, cuticle, nail matrix, nail bed, nail plate, and hyponychium. Distinguishing features are the shape of the nail and the presence of an extended hyponychium in the mouse [PMC3579226]</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>nail</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


