        <obo:IAO_0000115>Any of the layers that make up the retina[MP].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>MA does not treat internal/external limiting memranes as layers - these are classified as laminae. Here we follow other ontologies in grouping with other layers. MA also treats retinal pigment epithelium and neural retina epithelium as distinct from the layers. We follow ontologies such as FMA and ZFA in first dividing into pigmented and neural layers - these are also classified as layers, giving us over the usual 10 layers</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://linkedlifedata.com/resource/umls/id/C0459649"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C49328"/>
