        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#uberon_slim"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Snakes and limbless lizards typically possess only the right lung as a major respiratory organ; the left lung is greatly reduced, or even absent. Amphisbaenians, however, have the opposite arrangement, with a major left lung, and a reduced or absent right lung [WP]</rdfs:comment>
