        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An organ that aids digestion and stores bile produced by the liver[WP].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>Membranous muscular sac in which the bile from the liver remains stored until it is required. [Dorian_AF, Elsevier&apos;s_encyclopaedic_dictionary_of_medicine, Part_B:_Anatomy_(1988)_Amsterdam_etc.:_Elsevier][VHOG]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>Organ attached to the liver which stores bile and empties into the duodenum via the bile duct as needed for digestion.[AAO]</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000002>relationship type change: differentiates_from endoderm (AAO:0000139) CHANGED TO: develops_from endoderm (UBERON:0000925)[AAO]</obo:UBPROP_0000002>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000003>The presence of a gallbladder appears to be a primitive trait. It is found in most fish and all adult reptiles and amphibians and has been well conserved in mammals, for the most part.[well established][VHOG]</obo:UBPROP_0000003>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gallbladder"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://linkedlifedata.com/resource/umls/id/C0016976"/>
