        <obo:IAO_0000115>The cavity within the body of all animals higher than the coelenterates and certain primitive worms, formed by the splitting of the embryonic mesoderm into two layers. In mammals it forms the peritoneal, pleural, and pericardial cavities.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>check the FMA placement here; ncit placement of body cavity here probably not correct</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>Anatomical space, part of the trunk that contains the pericardial and pleuroperitoneal cavities[ZFA].</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>The cavity within the body of all animals higher than the coelenterates and certain primitive worms, formed by the splitting of the embryonic mesoderm into two layers. In mammals it forms the peritoneal, pleural, and pericardial cavities[BTO].</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000008>In mammals it forms the peritoneal, pleural, and pericardial cavities</obo:UBPROP_0000008>
