        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#vertebrate_core"/>
        <rdfs:comment>WP:Heart states: &quot;The SA node is found in all amniotes but not in more primitive vertebrates. In these animals, the muscles of the heart are relatively continuous and the sinus venosus coordinates the beat which passes in a wave through the remaining chambers. Indeed, since the sinus venosus is incorporated into the right atrium in amniotes, it is likely homologous with the SA node. In teleosts, with their vestigial sinus venosus, the main centre of coordination is, instead, in the atrium.&quot;. Note however that ZFA has SA node.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>sinoatrial node</rdfs:label>
        <foaf:depicted_by rdf:resource="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d2/Sinoatrial_node_low_mag.jpg"/>
        <foaf:depicted_by rdf:resource="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/de/Sinoatrial_node_2_low_mag.jpg"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


