        <obo:IAO_0000115>The inner serous membrane of the pulmonary pleural. The visceral pleura lines the lungs.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>Each lung is invested by an exceedingly delicate serous membrane, the pleura, which is arranged in the form of a closed invaginated sac. A portion of the serous membrane covers the surface of the lung and dips into the fissures between its lobes; it is called the pulmonary pleura (or visceral pleura). The visceral pleura is attached directly to the lungs[Wikipedia:Visceral_pleura].</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>FMA treats this as part of the lungs</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://linkedlifedata.com/resource/umls/id/C0225776"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C33881"/>
