        <obo:IAO_0000115>Anatomical structure that is part of the head consisting entirely of cranium and mandible[WP].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:RO_0002175 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7762"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>in FMA the skull is divided into orbit, neurocranium (8 parts), viscerocranium (26 parts). Here we have a separate overlapping division into cranium and mandible.</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000012>in many ontologies, the structure called the cranium is inclusive of the mandible/lower jaw skeleton</obo:UBPROP_0000012>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000013>A skull that is missing a mandible is only a cranium; this is the source of a very commonly made error in terminology. Those animals having skulls are called craniates</obo:UBPROP_0000013>
