        <obo:IAO_0000116>we make the germ layer relationship develops_from, as currently the germ layers are declared to be purely embryonic. TODO - check. WP:Amnion - In the human embryo the earliest stages of the formation of the amnion have not been observed; in the youngest embryo which has been studied the amnion was already present as a closed sac, and appears in the inner cell-mass as a cavity. This cavity is roofed in by a single stratum of flattened, ectodermal cells, the amniotic ectoderm, and its floor consists of the prismatic ectoderm of the embryonic disk-the continuity between the roof and floor being established at the margin of the embryonic disk. Outside the amniotic ectoderm is a thin layer of mesoderm, which is continuous with that of the somatopleure and is connected by the body-stalk with the mesodermal lining of the chorion.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>UBERON:0008359</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>BTO:0000897</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>EHDAA2:0000117</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>EHDAA:138</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>EMAPA:16110</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>VHOG:0000621</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>amnion ectoderm</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>amnionic ectoderm</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>uberon</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>amnion epithelium</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>UBERON:0003254</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:label>amniotic ectoderm</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


