        <obo:IAO_0000115>The funnel-like expansion of the abdominal extremity of the uterine tube[MP]</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <obo:RO_0002175 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_8782"/>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>The third part of the uterine tube is the infundibulum. It terminates with the ostium of Fallopian tube, surrounded by fimbriae, one of which is attached to the ovary[Wikipedia:Infundibulum_of_uterine_tube].</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
