        <obo:IAO_0000115>A set of structures containing cerebrospinal fluid in the brain. It is continuous with the central canal of the spinal cord[WP].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>TODO - resolve space vs structure conflation. We follow FMA in making this and the various ventricles a structure - it follows from this that strutures such as the tela choroidea and choroid plexuses can be part of the ventricles and ventricular system. Note: see also the class &apos;neuraxis cavity&apos;</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon.owl"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref rdf:resource="http://braininfo.rprc.washington.edu/centraldirectory.aspx?ID=2497"/>
