        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The splanchnic mesoderm in the cardiogenic region where the heart develops; it gives rise to endocardial heart tubes that fuse to form the primordial cardiac tube, the heart primordium[web]. Two migratory heart primordia that move ventrally during the course of neurulation, and then fuse[XAO].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>consider FBbt:00005541 ! cardiogenic mesoderm</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>review EHDAA2 placement</obo:IAO_0000116>
