        <obo:IAO_0000115>A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of a single digit plus the associated metapodial element.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>this class represents a series of phalanges plus a metapodial element. In comparative anatomy terminology we would call this a &apos;digit&apos;, but the label &apos;digit&apos; is sometimes used to exclude metapodials and to include soft tissue. This series of elements is hypothesized to be homologous to radials.</obo:IAO_0000232>
